13 DEFINITIONS.
14 As used in this act:
15 1. “Collaborative law communication” means a statement, whether
16 oral or in a record, or verbal or nonverbal, that:
17 a. is made to conduct, participate in, continue, or
18 reconvene a collaborative law process, and
19 b. occurs after the parties sign a collaborative law
20 participation agreement and before the collaborative
21 law process is concluded;
22 2. “Collaborative law participation agreement” means an
23 agreement by persons to participate in a collaborative law process;
24
